    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In Chinese culture, where one lives (住) is closely tied to family, stability, and social status.\nThe concept of 住 encompasses not just physical dwelling but also belonging to a community and\nestablishing roots."}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Traditional Chinese architecture emphasized the 住 concept through courtyard houses (四合院) where\nmultiple generations would 住 together, reinforcing family bonds and hierarchy."}],"type":"paragraph"}
